comment:
Whoa what.... the actual f---

It's heartbreaking to see Depp having to go through all of these; losing roles for his career, having so many people turned against him, being physically, emotionally and mentally hurt. However one thing the public can learn about this is to break off the stereotype that men cannot be abused or that men who are abused are weak that they should 'man up'. Victims of domestic abuse mustn't be discriminated regardless of their gender. Abuse is abuse, and abusers must face the law, even if the abuser is a charming, beautiful, innocent looking woman. Most importantly, the survivor's well is what matters the most and in this case I'm glad that Johny Depp didn't went through further unimaginable abuse and got his justice back.

#MeToo #Justice for Johny Depp
